# 090 — AI Agents

## LLM access

- All LLM calls must go through `packages/llm-gateway`. No direct `openai`, `anthropic`, or `mistral` SDK calls outside of `llm-gateway`.
- `llm-gateway` is the only package that imports provider SDKs.

## Prompts

- Prompts are versioned artifacts stored in the artifact store or a dedicated prompt registry.
- No hardcoded prompt strings in agent implementations — reference a prompt by ID and version.

## Outputs

- Agent outputs must be structured and validated with a Zod schema before use.
- `AgentResult` shape: `{ artifacts: Artifact[]; blockers: Blocker[]; approvalRequests: ApprovalRequest[]; confidence: number; reasoning: string }`.

## Safety

- Agents must not bypass approval gates.
- Agents must not self-approve their own outputs.
- Agents must not make authoritative claims in domains requiring human judgment: legal, medical, security policy, privacy decisions.
- Any output flagged with `requiresHumanReview: true` must be routed to an approval gate before downstream nodes consume it.

## Prompt injection defense

- User-supplied content passed to an agent must be wrapped in explicit delimiters in the prompt template.
- Agent implementations must document which parts of their prompt are user-controlled.